review_text:
Posted: August 12
This is a truly revolutionary third-person action RPG set in a depressing dark fantasy world. This was my first time playing, and I finally understand all the hype. I can truly appreciate all its genius and influence. The challenging but fair combat in a very atmospheric setting was my main selling point. If you're still on the fence, don't be discouraged. It's not overly difficult, and you don't need a controller to enjoy it, so give it a try!

Pros:
- Very interesting multiplayer system;
- Good optimization;
- Memorable characters;
- Great visuals;
- Interesting lore;
- Outstanding combat system;
- Great enemy variety and design;
- Awesome soundtrack;
- Great art design;
- Attention to details;
- An atmospheric world;
- Outstanding level design;
- Great replayability;
- Unique and interesting storytelling;

Cons:
- The controls for keyboard and mouse could be much better.

Posted: March 7
This game is like my Ex;
Toxic, but I'll go back to it anyway.
